text: My pre-ordered @Apple #iPhoneXS (to date) has spent 20.5 hours with @UPS in China, 2 days 7 hours in Louisville, apparently some time in Hong Kong, 1 day 22 hours in Anchorage, now going on 12.5 hours back in Louisville. Perfectly acceptable though, according to #Apple and #UPS.
@MorrisarUF I know how frustrating it can be to have a package delayed that you have been waiting on. We are working on getting these shipments delivered as quickly as possible. ^AC

@UPSHelp Problem isn't frustration. It's that @UPS promises guaranteed time-in-transit times with #UPS World Ease and doesn't deliver. What message does that send to businesses? And @Apple promises that #iPhoneXS will arrive on the release date. What message does that send to customers? https://t.co/mtAo6cpvOd
